Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

There are currently no commercial options available to return to the UK from Algeria.
As of 19 March, all international flights to and from Algeria were suspended, including flights to the UK. All land borders are now closed and ferry services are suspended.
We know this is concerning for British people trying to leave Algeria. The UK government is working closely with airlines, the Algerian authorities and other governments to make sure options are available for you to return to the UK as soon as possible.
What to do
If you’re a British national normally resident in the UK, visiting Algeria, you should email Consular Services at the British Embassy in Algiers with your contact details. For each person in your party please provide:
name and date of birth
passport number
current location
contact details (email and telephone)
and if you hold another nationality please stipulate which
We will not reply to individual emails, but we will be able to contact you when we have further information.
If you cannot leave Algeria at this time, you should:
follow the advice of local authorities, including local measures to help minimise your risk of exposure to coronavirus.
find accommodation that’s suitable for your needs.
keep in regular contact with family and friends at home, so they know you are safe and well.
Future travel options
The UK government is working closely with airlines, the Algerian authorities and other governments to make sure options are available for you to return to the UK as soon as possible.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts for Algeria and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy at algiers.consular@fco.gov.uk or call 0770085000.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for email alerts for Algeria travel advice.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
